FBIS4-16221 "drsov072_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 National Affairs Crimea's Meshkov Criticizes Decision on Representative Crimea's Meshkov Criticizes Decision on Representative AU1304134394 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 12 Apr 94 p 1 AU1304134394 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY Ukrainian BFN [Report attributed to the BBC] [Text] President of the Crimean Autonomous Republic Yuriy Meshkov subjected the decision by the Ukrainian president to create the institution of Ukrainian presidential representative in the Crimea to sharp criticism. In his televised speech, Meshkov called the Ukrainian Government "the most dangerous in Europe." He pointed out that the appointment of such a representative is a political provocation, which may do harm to the development of the democratic process on the peninsula. This was reported by the BBC.
